What is Spring MVC?
- It is web framework build around spring basics. It can be unit tested.
- It is very light weight. JSF is very weight, you have to do things their way.
- Based on front controller pattern
- Built around Struts
- Annotation Based Configuration
- Seamless integration with other Spring projects

Incoming Request -> Servlet Container -> Dispatch to one of our controllers -> Backend

Dispatcher Servlet-  Entry Point
Controller - Handles the request and route to
Request Mapping - URL, Request Type
ViewResolver - Locate JSP Page
Servlet Config - Configuration per Dispatcher Servlet
Bean - Spring Configured Bean
POJO - Plain Old Java Object

Spring MVC 
